text: Kaczki (German Katzke, Kaski) is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Trąbki Wielkie, within Gdańsk County, Pomeranian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately east of Trąbki Wielkie, south-west of Pruszcz Gdański, and south of the regional capital Gdańsk. For details of the history of the region, see History of Pomerania. The village has a population of 254. == People == * Heinrich Czolbe ==References== Kaczki
